#Filling the null values of Numerical column(Rating) with the Median value
def subs_median(series):
    return series.fillna(series.median())
In [732]:
ds.Rating=ds.Rating.transform(subs_median)

#Filling the Categorical column- Type having null values with the Mode value
#Typecasted to str because ds.Type.mode().values[0] accepts numerical values
ds.Type.fillna(str(ds.Type.mode().values[0]),inplace=True)
#values[0] so that it will consider the first value in case of bimodal columns
#Applying inplace=True so that the change will be applied to the dataframe; fillna by default has inplace=False
In [736]:
#Filling the Categorical column- Current Ver having null values with the Mode value
